---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About DealMela"
  description="How DealMela curates deals, why every listing carries an editorial note, and what we'll never do to earn a click."
>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-4 sm:px-6 pt-10 sm:pt-14 pb-20">
    <h1 class="font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-semibold text-ink mb-6">About DealMela</h1>

    <div class="prose-like text-ink-soft leading-relaxed space-y-5 text-[15px] sm:text-base">
      <p>
        DealMela exists for one reason: to save you the ten minutes you'd otherwise spend cross-checking whether a "deal" is actually a deal. We browse Amazon, Flipkart, and a handful of other Indian retailers, and we only publish a listing when the price genuinely stands out.
      </p>
      <p>
        We are not a store. You can't buy anything from us directly, there's no cart, and we never ask for an account or an email address just to see a price. Every "View Deal" button takes you to the retailer's own page, where you complete the purchase — we simply earn a small commission if you do, at no extra cost to you.
      </p>
      <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-ink pt-2">How a listing gets picked</h2>
      <p>
        Every product on DealMela is reviewed by a person before it's published, and carries a short "Why we picked this" note explaining the actual reason it made the cut — a genuine strength, a price that's unusually low for the spec, or a detail competitors get wrong. If we can't write an honest sentence about why something is worth your click, it doesn't go up.
      </p>
      <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-ink pt-2">What we won't do</h2>
      <p>
        No countdown timers that reset when you refresh the page. No "only 2 left" unless the retailer's own listing says so. No pop-ups asking you to sign up before you can see a price. Ratings and review counts shown here are always the retailer's own numbers, clearly labeled as such — never ours, never invented.
      </p>
      <p>
        Questions, corrections, or a deal you think we should feature? Reach us on the <a href="/contact" class="text-brick underline underline-offset-2">Contact</a> page.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
